.Dd $Mdocdate: December 6 2019 $
.Dt UVM_VSLOCK 9
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm uvm_vslock ,
.Nm uvm_vsunlock
.Nd wire user memory for I/O
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.In uvm/uvm_extern.h
.Ft void
.Fn uvm_vslock "struct proc *p" "caddr_t addr" "size_t len" \
               "vm_prot_t access_type"
.Ft void
.Fn uvm_vsunlock "struct proc *p" "caddr_t addr" "size_t len"
.Sh DESCRIPTION
The
.Fn uvm_vslock
and
.Fn uvm_vsunlock
functions control the wiring and unwiring of pages for process
.Fa p
from
.Fa addr
to
.Fa addr + len .
The
.Fa access_type
argument of
.Fn uvm_vslock
is passed to
.Xr uvm_fault 9 .
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr uvm_fault 9
